Interface Fillable

All Known Subinterfaces:
ByteBufferFillable
All Known Implementing Classes:
ByteBufferObject
public interface Fillable
A fillable object needs to be filled with data. It may also have owned properties or objects that also need to be filled with data. A type must be fillable if it is to be traversed to find other fillable elements. Fillable elements should expect to have whatever data they contain be replaced when they are filled.
